Sadao Watanabe (渡辺 貞夫, Watanabe Sadao, born February 1, 1933) is a Japanese jazz musician who plays alto saxophone, sopranino saxophone, and flute.
Watanabe was born on 1 February 1933 in Utsunomiya, Japan.
Watanabe learned the clarinet while in high school after convincing his father over the course of six weeks to buy him a second-hand instrument.
He started studying the flute in 1953 with Ririko Hayashi from the Tokyo Philharmonic Orchestra.
He played with the John Coltrane quintet in Tokyo while the group was touring Japan 1966.
By the time he played at the 1970 Newport Jazz Festival he has was a well-known and often highly-regarded jazz performer.
Watanabe continued performing and recording through the 1970s and 1980s, amassing a catalogue of more than 70 albums as leader.
In addition to his musical career, Sadao Watanabe has published six photography books in Japan.
